  "notes": [
    "COLLEGE ADMISSIONS REQUIREMENTS FOR TRANSFER STUDENTS THIS MAJOR IS OFFERED BY THE COLLEGE OF LETTERS AND SCIENCE (L&S) IMPORTANT information for students applying for admission to L&S for the fall 2025 application cycle and beyond Completion of Essential Skills requirements (Reading & Composition, Quantitative Reasoning, and Foreign Language) or Cal-GETC/IGETC will no longer be a requirement for admission; however, completion of either is strongly recommended prior to enrollment at UC Berkeley to ensure timely degree progress. More information on new polices is available on the L&S Transfer Student Applicants website. By the end of the spring term preceding fall enrollment at Berkeley, you must complete : 1) The 7-course pattern (as found in the UC Transfer Admission Eligibility Courses Menu in ASSIST): · Two transferable courses in English composition; · One transferable course in mathematical concepts and quantitative reasoning; · Four transferable college courses chosen from at least two of the following subject areas: o arts and humanities o social and behavioral sciences o physical and biological sciences AND 2) Major Requirements : Follow the guidance on preparation for this major below. For more information on L&S General Education requirements: For information on courses that will satisfy L&S General Education (Essential Skills and Seven-Course Breadth) requirements from your community college complete the following steps: Go to \"Search below for articulation agreements: Major, department, and campus-specific general education agreements” Click on the down arrow to select: Academic Year, Institution: UC Berkeley , and Agreements with Other Institutions: (Your CA Community College). Click on “View Agreements”. Under “View Agreement by” select “ General Education/Breadth ”. Click on the “General Education/Breadth” radio button, then click on “View Agreement” Learn more from the UC Berkeley Office of Undergraduate Admission and specifically about transfer admission preparation. Review all available majors at UC Berkeley .",
    "Fall 2026 Admission for this Major: Transfer students who select this major on their College of Letters and Science (L&S) application and are offered admission to L&S will be directly admitted into this major. If you are interested in this major, it is very important to select this major on your application, and complete as many lower-division major requirements as possible prior to transfer. See details on preparation for this major below. - Select two from the following lists: A,B,C. Only one course can count from each list. Required for admission. - Math List A: MATH 16A, MATH 51, MATH 53, MATH 54, MATH 55. Only one of MATH 16A or MATH 51 can be used for the major. - Math List B: MATH 16B, MATH 52, MATH 53, MATH 54, MATH 55. Only one of MATH 16B or MATH 52 can be used for the major. - Math List C: STAT 2, STAT 20, DATA C8. - Biology 1A and 1AL. Required for admission. - Biology 1B. Required for admission. - Chem 1A and 1AL. Strongly Recommended for admission, required for graduation. For students pursuing health careers, it's recommended to have already completed a year of organic chemistry with lab prior to starting at UC Berkeley. - Physics 8A or 7A. Strongly Recommended for admission, required for graduation. Retain all syllabi (including which reference materials and textbooks were used, methods of assessment, learning objectives, and lecture/topic schedules). Unarticulated courses and series must be reviewed by the respective Berkeley department – a course description is insufficient for review. Students must initiate the review process by contacting Integrative Biology academic advisors after admission. A 2.0 combined major GPA is required. All major requirements must be taken for a letter grade. Split series articulations not taken on the same campus are not accepted, even from within the same system. Split series must be reviewed independently. Students are encouraged to take INTEGBI 77A or 77B their first semester for an introduction to the department’s faculty, research, and courses. It’s also a good opportunity to meet students with similar interests and build community.",
    "Exam credit is not accepted in lieu of required or recommended courses for this major.",
    "Integrative Biology spans hierarchical levels from molecules to ecosystems, incorporating many diverse disciplines to unravel the complexity of biology. The department embraces discovery-based approaches to student learning, encouraging independent research and scientific community engagement. Students in Integrative Biology choose specialized upper division courses, with help from academic advisors, that match their interests. Course variety includes field-based organismal biology and evolution, quantitative and population genetics and genomics, animal behavior, paleontology, anatomy, and physiology. Integrative Biology’s focus on comparative biology and evolution provides a lens for understanding our interconnected living world. For more information about the full major requirements, sample plans, and student opportunities, visit us at: Web: https://ib.berkeley.edu/undergrad Email: ibusso@berkeley.edu Office: 3060 Valley Life Sciences Building Phone: 510-643-8895"
  ]
